-- Scottish support for independence rises to 48 pct - Opinium poll
-- 
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 04:16PM EDT
-- None



EDINBURGH, Sept 16 (Reuters) - Scottish support for independence has risen one percentage point to 48 percent, an Opinium poll for the Daily Telegraph newspaper showed on Tuesday.

The poll showed Scottish support for staying in the United Kingdom on 52 percent, down from 53 percent from its last poll at the weekend, the Telegraph said.